{
  "doc_id": "37092",
  "text": "For the past decade, researchers developed a variety of constraint solvers [CITATION_1] . Among them, Z3 [CITATION_2] is one of the most powerful constraint solvers with features of supporting linear real and integer arithmetic, fixed-size bit-vector, uninterpreted functions, extensional arrays, quantifiers, multiple input formats, and extensive APIs (including C/C ++/.NET/Java/Python APIs). Z3-str [CITATION_3] is an extension of Z3 supporting combined logics over strings and non-string operations. It supports three sorts of logic: (i) string-sorted terms include string constants and variables of arbitrary length; (ii) integer-sorted terms are standard, with the exception of the length function over string terms; (iii) Boolean operators are used to combine atomic formulas which are equations over string terms and equalities or inequalities over integer terms. In this paper, we leverage advances in constraint solvers and use Z3 and Z3-str as constraint solver to generate the relevant input values of a path condition, which is to be discussed later.",
